.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn mad_new
function return
.Va NULL
on failure and allocates memory that has to be freed using
.Fn mad_free
on success.
Unless stated otherwise, all other functions return a value greater than or equal to
.Va 0
on success or
.Va -1
on failure.
